the sea under so much surveillance.

171
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:19,170
Now I understand. But...

172
00:14:19,170 --> 00:14:22,730
I wouldn't have gone to the coast anyway.

173
00:14:23,780 --> 00:14:28,510
If you're worried about the invitation,
it'll be alright if I take the blame!

174
00:14:28,510 --> 00:14:30,760
If you attend the wedding, that'll be it!

175
00:14:30,760 --> 00:14:33,200
Since Mama is so used to political marriages,

176
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:36,440
she puts bracelets on brides and grooms 
who are likely to escape.

177
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:39,300
If you try to get off
the island with them...

178
00:14:39,300 --> 00:14:41,580
They'll explode.

179
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:41,580
Huh?

180
00:14:45,180 --> 00:14:47,490
Your mom has the key to them.

181
00:14:47,490 --> 00:14:51,710
To get that, I'd have to defeat 
the Big Mom Pirates.

182
00:14:51,710 --> 00:14:54,010
Don't tell me Mama has already...

183
00:14:54,010 --> 00:15:00,120
Yeah, she's already made
those arrangements, and besides...

184
00:15:03,090 --> 00:15:06,340
I don't have a single ally around me.

185
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:16,390
Even though we're related by blood...

186
00:15:21,490 --> 00:15:23,560
This is what they've done.

187
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:28,030
Did your real family hurt you like that?

188
00:15:28,030 --> 00:15:29,250
Yeah.

189
00:15:29,650 --> 00:15:31,990
How could they...

190
00:15:32,620 --> 00:15:38,450
It seems like I'm a failure to them,
and they can't stand my existence.

191
00:15:39,790 --> 00:15:44,150
I've never even once thought
that I was happy to be born royal.

192
00:15:47,760 --> 00:15:50,610
That's why I set out to sea...

193
00:15:51,130 --> 00:15:54,470
to find a place I wasn't even sure existed.

194
00:15:56,020 --> 00:15:57,100
But...

195
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:02,870
if I resist the marriage,

196
00:16:04,560 --> 00:16:07,610
my friends and I will be all dead.

197
00:16:07,610 --> 00:16:09,320
On top of that,

198
00:16:09,320 --> 00:16:15,450
they'll kill my real father in the East Blue,
a man I'm deeply indebted to!

199
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:20,450
Wherever I look, I have no way out.

200
00:16:20,910 --> 00:16:22,220
So...

201
00:16:23,890 --> 00:16:26,540
I decided to stop resisting!

202
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:35,580
On the condition that I accept this marriage,

203
00:16:35,580 --> 00:16:38,760
I want Big Mom to let my friends go.

204
00:16:43,520 --> 00:16:46,600
They're going after Luffy and the others.

205
00:16:48,040 --> 00:16:50,230
I'm sorry!

206
00:16:50,230 --> 00:16:54,070
My mother put you 
in such a difficult position!

207
00:16:54,750 --> 00:16:56,210
Stop!

208
00:16:56,210 --> 00:16:58,620
It's not your fault!

209
00:16:58,620 --> 00:16:59,530
But...

210
00:17:02,680 --> 00:17:08,060
Thirteen years ago... I was in hell.

211
00:17:08,060 --> 00:17:11,160
Now I'm back in it.

212
00:17:11,740 --> 00:17:17,090
I should be happy to have been away
from here as long as 13 years.

213
00:17:17,090 --> 00:17:20,680
The people who let me
polish my cooking skills

214
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:23,890
and the friends who I traveled with...

215
00:17:24,990 --> 00:17:28,810
I'm indebted to everyone that I met.

216
00:17:29,450 --> 00:17:32,480
I just wanna go away without hurting anyone.

217
00:17:34,460 --> 00:17:38,030
My adventure ends here.

218
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:48,920
Hey, don't cry.
It makes me feel pathetic!

219
00:17:49,750 --> 00:17:51,570
I...

220
00:17:55,100 --> 00:17:56,760
Sanji-san !

221
00:17:57,760 --> 00:18:02,600
I won't let your marriage with me be hell!

222
00:18:10,230 --> 00:18:16,110
I'm sorry! What am I saying?!
You're deeply suffering!

223
00:18:16,110 --> 00:18:20,280
The unwanted marriage
should be hell to you, too!

224
00:18:20,280 --> 00:18:23,240
How could I say such a thing
when someone's in pain?!

225
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:25,830
I'm ashamed of myself! I'm sorry!

226
00:18:25,830 --> 00:18:32,130
I've only known you for a short time!
There's no way I can fill the hole in your heart!

227
00:18:32,130 --> 00:18:37,620
In the first place, you didn't even say
that you're gonna marry me!

228
00:18:37,620 --> 00:18:39,300
I'm so...

229
00:19:11,080 --> 00:19:14,670
You're my... salvation.

230
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:18,210
Sanji-san...

231
00:19:19,170 --> 00:19:22,140
If I'm good enough for you...

232
00:19:23,840 --> 00:19:27,440
Let's get married tomorrow.

233
00:19:36,320 --> 00:19:38,820
Thanks for all the damage.

234
00:19:39,710 --> 00:19:41,150
What is this?!

235
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:43,490
Get down here!

236
00:19:54,150 --> 00:19:55,700
